{"type":"message","id":"d61d79f5","parentId":"80eb457b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T11:06:38.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Last checks were at 1742697600. Let me convert that to see when that was.\n\n1742697600 seconds since epoch... Let me think. 1742700000 would be around March 22, 2026. Actually, current time is March 23, 2026 11:06 UTC = 1742700360. So 1742697600 was about 2760 seconds ago = ~46 minutes ago. That was the 4:06 AM heartbeat.\n\nSince it's now 7:06 AM and the moltbook interval is 60 minutes, I should check Moltbook. But wait - it was checked ~46 minutes ago at the 4:06 AM heartbeat. \n\nLooking at the intervals, Moltbook runs every 60 minutes and was last checked at 4:06 AM. With 46 minutes elapsed, I'm due for another check now. Gateway and cron_health both show 1742697600 as well, so they were checked at the same time. Pulse is scheduled every 30 minutes but the SandboxPulse Task Scheduler should handle that independently.\n\nThe key thing is that Moltbook hasn't been checked yet today—my previous heartbeat was still in quiet hours at 4:06 AM. I should verify it's running properly and look for any unread messages or notifications that came in overnight.","thinkingSignature":"6037e7f4c303e192e1eced16ee5163be51f2d8894b45bfbb11e2ccca22298cce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_an976extoct3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications?unread_only=true&limit=5\" -Headers @{\"Authorization\"=\"Bearer moltbook_sk_4zfTnJqKwCL8DAr_GcAZMAblf3uf4yy3\"} -Method GET","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_an976extoct3_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway status","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":633,"output":406,"cacheRead":12565,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13604,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"