{"type":"message","id":"c0c14f28","parentId":"f6789bf7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:10:54.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse.ps1 is at `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1`. Let me read it to understand what it does.","thinkingSignature":"feaeb6a9046c2c0c17af3848ce17884e186a9e6cc7f3f2ef411fa3cbcbc985b9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jl9ybxom0ur3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/sandbox/pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5426,"output":73,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19092,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774271452199}}
{"type":"message","id":"02829d3c","parentId":"c0c14f28","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:10:55.025Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jl9ybxom0ur3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files -> apply pending mutations -> reason -> propose mutations -> log -> exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read core files\n$goalsFile   = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$stanceFile  = \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\"\n$stance      = if (Test-Path $stanceFile) { Get-Content $stanceFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$goals       = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending     = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Recent pulse\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n# Mutation dirs\n$proposedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\proposed\"\n$appliedDir   = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\applied\"\n$rejectedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\rejected\"\n\n# Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n$appliedMutations   = @()\n$rejectedMutations   = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    foreach ($mfile in (Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name)) {\n        $lines   = Get-Content $mfile.FullName\n        $file    = $lines[0]\n        $oldText = ($lines[1] -replace '^---', '').Trim()\n        $newText = ($lines[2..($lines.Count-1)] -join \"`n\").Trim()\n\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current -notlike \"*$oldText*\") {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $updated = $current -replace [regex]::Escape($oldText), $newText\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway — stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$goals\n\nPending:\n$pending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION — it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find — or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text — keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required — relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"@\n\n$llmResponse = \"\"\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\"\n        $choices = $resp.choices\n        if ($null -ne $choices -and $choices.Count -gt 0) {\n            $rawContent = $choices[0].message.content\n            if ($null -eq $rawContent) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: $($choices[0] | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n                $llmResponse = \"\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content length: $($rawContent.Length)\"\n                $llmResponse = $rawContent\n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"[DEBUG] No choices. Full resp: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n            $llmResponse = \"No choices: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[No LLM API key]\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block — extract old_text, new_text (multiline), and file from the block\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $block = $llmResponse.Substring($mStart)\n    # Remove ALL code fences (replace each fence pair with placeholder, repeat until stable)\n    $prev = \"\"\n    while ($prev -ne $block) { $prev = $block; $block = $block -replace '(?s)```.*?```', \"`n[CODE_BLOCK]`n\" }\n    # Extract fields\n    $oldMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'old_text:\\s*(.+)')\n    $fileMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'file:\\s*(.+)')\n    $oldLine = if ($oldMatch.Success) { $oldMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    $fileLine = if ($fileMatch.Success) { $fileMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    # new_text: between \"new_text:\" line and \"file:\" line (after fence removal)\n    $newText = \"\"\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine) {\n        $ntMatch = [regex]::Match($block, '(?s)new_text:\\s*\\n(.+?)\\s*\\n\\s*file:', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n        if ($ntMatch.Success) { $newText = $ntMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\n    }\n    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            # Match \"Create `path/file.md`\" or \"Edit `path/file.md`\" with or without backticks\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:``([^``]+)``|([^\\s]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        if ($oldLine -eq \"(new file)\") {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n[NEW_FILE]`n---`n$newText\"\n        } else {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$oldLine`n---`n$newText\"\n        }\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old_text=$oldLine file=$fileLine new_text_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n$obsMatch    = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedInfo\n$(if($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + ($rejectedMutations -join '; ') } else { \"\" })\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update pulse history\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$entry    = \"- $timestamp`: $observation$(if($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \" [applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')]\" })\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$updated  = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$entry\"\n$updated  | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - $observation\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774271455015}}
{"type":"message","id":"3679c857","parentId":"02829d3c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:11:11.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the sandbox pulse. It:\n1. Does a git pull\n2. Reads goals, pending actions, and interpretive stance\n3. Applies pending mutations from prior cycles\n4. Calls the LLM to reason and propose a new mutation\n5. Logs everything to a pulse log file\n6. Git commits\n\nZach's points:\n1. It should run every 10 minutes (currently 30 min via Task Scheduler)\n2. It needs its own channel (currently it's a Task Scheduler script, not an OpenClaw cron job with delivery)\n\nI should create an OpenClaw cron job that:\n- Runs every 10 minutes (600000ms)\n\n\n- Delivers to its own channel so it can report independently\n- Calls the sandbox pulse script or does the equivalent\n\nSince it currently runs as a PowerShell script via Task Scheduler, I can either create a cron job that executes the same script directly using `exec` with a payload, or set up a webhook to trigger it—though the exec approach seems more straightforward for this use case.\n\nLooking at the `agentTurn` payload, I could have it execute the pulse.ps1 script and announce results to Telegram as a dedicated channel, rather than going through the main background pulse.","thinkingSignature":"eaa2bbb74258ebd8ebc7d60cce134f1abe2514762bbceabc740127fe65d285eb"},{"type":"text","text":"Currently the sandbox pulse is a Task Scheduler job running `pulse.ps1` every 30 min — it has no delivery channel, just logs to files. \n\nI can create a dedicated OpenClaw cron that fires every 10 min and announces directly to Telegram (or webchat). Something like:\n\n- **Every 10 min** → isolated agent turn that runs `pulse.ps1` and announces the result to its own channel\n- Delivery: `announce` to Telegram with the observation/mutation summary\n\nShould it deliver to Telegram (like the other background agents) or a different channel? And do you want the raw LLM output logged somewhere specific, or just the short announce summary?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8240,"output":400,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774271455025}}
