{"type":"message","id":"e6dcbad8","parentId":"6a03d5ea","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:19:18.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bot is `@hedgehogclawbot`. Now I need to figure out how to set up a dedicated channel for sandbox updates. \n\nThe bot has been added as a new Telegram account in the config. Now I need to:\n1. Create a dedicated cron job that fires every 10 mins\n2. Have it announce to this new bot channel (or a chat associated with it)\n\nThe tricky part is: how do I route messages to the new bot/channel? The cron jobs currently deliver to `telegram` channel with a `to` field of a user ID. But the new bot needs its own Telegram user ID... \n\nActually, since the new bot is a separate Telegram bot, I can set up a channel entry for it in the config. \n\nI see the new bot is configured in the channels section. For a bot to send messages, it needs to be added to a group or have a direct conversation initiated with it first. Zach would need to message @hedgehogclawbot on Telegram to start a conversation, then I can retrieve the chat ID and configure the channel properly.\n\nOnce that's set up, I can create a cron job targeting this new bot's channel for sandbox pulses. Let me ask Zach to message the bot first so I can get the chat ID.","thinkingSignature":"2d4aa446103210f14051efb10b735027f54835049d1ef10b041824d3005fea7c"},{"type":"text","text":"Bot is `@hedgehogclawbot`. To route the sandbox pulse to it, I need to send it a message first (start a conversation so Telegram gives it a chat ID). \n\nGo open `@hedgehogclawbot` in Telegram and send it any message — just a \"/start\" or \"hi\". Then let me know when it's done and I'll grab the chat ID and wire up the 10-min sandbox pulse cron."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11874,"output":353,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25820,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total"