{"type":"message","id":"a544f9de","parentId":"1d8ec388","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:20:31.841Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The updates returned empty. This likely means the gateway is consuming the updates via webhook. Let me try a different approach - maybe the updates are being consumed by the gateway already. Let me check if the gateway has a webhook set up for this bot. Actually, I think the issue is that since the gateway is already polling or has a webhook for the main bot (8587631426:AAHvqmo--g25LqsClCWCXj4m617cn2v7V7Q), the new bot's updates might be getting consumed differently.\n\nLet me try to get updates with an offset to see if there's anything there.","thinkingSignature":"a12fbd0aed86f7f540698f950b77c2e5c2a9b9ab8a12220c89f758b4bf823a13"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j03a6tnc4zrf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Invoke-RestMethod \"https://api.telegram.org/bot7669304147:AAHVFq38PYGmS_Shc7bCxtMLUXyKE4_k6cU/getUpdates?limit=10&timeout=0\" -Method GET | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12049,"output":229,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25871,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774272025693}}
