{"type":"message","id":"75a0a1aa","parentId":"316e9731","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:20:42.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still empty. This could be because the gateway has a webhook set for the main bot, and this new bot doesn't have any updates yet because the gateway isn't configured to use this new bot. Or the updates are being consumed.\n\nActually, thinking about it - when I added the new bot with `openclaw channels add`, it was added with the \"default\" account name. But the gateway might be using webhooks for Telegram, and if there's already a webhook for the primary bot, maybe this new bot doesn't have updates coming through the same way.\n\nLet me try to send a message to the user using the new bot to verify the bot is working, and also check the gateway config to understand the webhook situation.\n\n\nSince the updates are empty, I should just attempt sending a message directly to Zach's Telegram ID (8371302588) using the new bot token to confirm it's functioning.","thinkingSignature":"4e01fb092f8c86dd1282a83aa826dae35bebd4ae5372b52bc10cec4d7b8a03f1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ri5jxzfmnvfv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Invoke-RestMethod \"https://api.telegram.org/bot7669304147:AAHVFq38PYGmS_Shc7bCxtMLUXyKE4_k6cU/sendMessage\" -Method POST -ContentType \"application/json\" -Body '{\"chat_id\": 8371302588, \"text\": \"Sandbox channel test 🦞\"}' | ConvertTo-Json","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12307,"output":298,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774272032905}}
