{"type":"message","id":"203fd842","parentId":"a2ca5d9e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:20:56.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The message was sent to Zach's Telegram (Ton0Fun). Now I have the chat ID: 8371302588 for the new bot.\n\nNow I can:\n1. Create a new cron job for sandbox pulse every 10 min, delivering to this new Telegram bot channel\n2. The channel is now configured and working\n\nLet me now create the 10-min sandbox pulse cron. The delivery will use this new bot's channel. I need to set up the delivery to go to `channel: \"telegram\"` with `to: \"8371302588\"` and it should use the new bot.\n\nActually, looking at the openclaw.json, there's only one Telegram bot configured. \n\nSince both the new bot and the original one are linked to the same Telegram account (8371302588), I need to figure out which bot the gateway will use for sending. The `channels.telegram` config currently specifies the original bot token, so I need to either add the new bot as a separate channel or update the config to use it instead.\n\nLooking at how the delivery system works, when I specify `channel: \"telegram\"` with a `to` field pointing to 8371302588, it should route to the configured bot. Since I've already added the new bot token to the config, the gateway should use it for sending. The session routing through `agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588` should continue to work as before.\n\nNow I'm setting up the 10-minute cron job to deliver sandbox pulses to this Telegram channel, using the new @hedgehogclawbot bot.","thinkingSignature":"eb9691e454cca83d376519f6eb186a7da95d5dc4a4826800a76a975d460536dd"},{"type":"text","text":"Bot's working — message sent to your Telegram. Now let me set up the 10-min sandbox pulse cron delivering to this channel:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ci3pika74q11_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"Sandbox-Pulse-10min","sessionTarget":"isolated","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the sandbox pulse and report the result.\n\nExecute: C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1\n\nRead the most recent pulse log from C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\ ( newest file ). Extract the OBSERVATION and any applied mutations. Reply with a concise summary of what happened in this pulse cycle.","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.5-Lightning","timeoutSeconds":120},"schedule":{"everyMs":600000,"kind":"every"},"delivery":{"channel":"telegram","mode":"announce","to":"8371302588"},"enabled":true}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12760,"output":581,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26934,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774272043710}}
