{"type":"message","id":"b2737d29","parentId":"caea2cb2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:28:50.556Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is confirming the old HP laptop would run Linux, not Windows. That makes total sense - Ubuntu Server would be perfect for it. Let me give him a concise response about this plan.","thinkingSignature":"e4c4dda2e065e382d658dfccef195589906094ca588843408aa6fc2884d27c3d"},{"type":"text","text":"Even better. Linux makes it easy. Ubuntu Server on 6GB RAM is no problem at all — Ubuntu Server itself idles at under 500MB, leaving plenty of room for OpenClaw + a small Ollama model.\n\nQuick rundown for the HP setup:\n\n- **OS:** Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS (free, minimal, well-documented)\n- **RAM usage:** ~400-600MB idle, ~2GB with a 7B model running via Ollama\n- **Storage:** Depends on the model — could fit a 7B quant in ~4GB, 13B in ~8GB\n- **Power:** Seriously low — could run 24/7 for <$10/month in electricity\n- **Network:** Just needs Wi-Fi or Ethernet, and you're on the same tailnet/VPN\n\nFor OpenClaw, you'd install it with a one-liner, point it at the gateway, and it's basically the same setup you have now — just running on the HP instead of your main machine.\n\n**Biggest wins:**\n- Always-on Nova — no dependency on your main machine being on\n- Could set up Tailscale (free) and access from anywhere\n- Home server for Ollama, file storage, etc.\n\nIf you want, I can prep the setup steps so they're ready when you get the laptop?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":319,"cacheRead":28712,"cacheWrite":176,"totalTokens":29250,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774272520569}}
